Honored to be a @gocampaign change maker. Inspired by their efforts to fund local organizations in LA like Avalon Carver in Watts and their local hero Jamico Elder. What we just did on the Live with the help of your donating has already changed a couple of kids lives for a couple of months with making sure they can participate in education, vocational training, health and safety. Thank you for helping us GO.
#gocampaign #watts #jamicoelder #avaloncarvercommunitycenter #goodtogo

node.text: Happy first night of Hanukkah , happy holidays. For each night of Hanukkah I will share a charity as well. It’s not meant to flood you with anxieties about feeling as if you have to give to every single one, or make you feel like you have to give at all... but to bring awareness and perspective to the holidays, they are not always a simple time or an abundant time for all. Especially this year, with businesses and families and health being impacted by a pandemic, there is a lot of hopelessness and fear surrounding this time, as we inch towards a new year, some of us very far from our families and loved ones, so, I will be sharing, to perchance inspire; giving back, being of service, and finding ways to make this holiday season special.

node.text:
Voting, to me, when everyone can vote fairly, is a clear example of our potential Freedom as Americans. It is a way to have our voices heard as a collective, it is a way to inspire and be a part of change. Each vote counts, even down to the Electoral College, it is our individual voices that make the difference. We have responsibilities as members of a Country to vote for our liberties and how the systems we live in function. Importantly, too, voting on a local level helps ensure that our voices and our belief systems are being looked after, supported and lifted. By electing our local Judges, DA officials, etc.; WE make this happen.
As many of us are sitting at home wondering if another stimulus check will come, if $1200 is a defining number of our worth, as people are sick and dying and COVID-19 cases rise, as many of us are beginning to wake up to the systemic racism we operate within, the level of white supremacy that runs rampant in our government, our wallets, and our current administration…we can only move towards a gradual progression in the other direction, a direction in a system that reflects a world that a community can imagine, a much more beautiful and caring world. My vote this election is my commitment to fighting for better options on the 2024 ballot, it is my commitment to fighting for my marginalized neighbors lives, it is a commitment to fight for human rights to not be a discussion that needs to be voted on, but something that is agreed as a given and essential in opening the doors to a future of possibilities and improvements that we are too blind to see now. 

Voting is about putting our worth out there, defining it for ourselves together, and letting a system know that we are here, we won’t settle, we have rights, and we will fight.

 Get ready to #VoteAboutIt on November 3rd. Check your registration status at the link in bio.

node.text:
TOMORROW at 3pm PST
@thandiweabdullah and I are going live on my insta.
“I guess I’ve been an organizer for some time” 
I’m so honored to get to know @thandiweabdullah, she is special and has been steeped in the fight for racial justice for a long time at 16 years old. Grateful she is going to do this, even if she refers to me as a millennial 🤪

ALSO, this is from a @blmlosangeles protest that takes place every Wednesday. If you are in LA, you should show up, find out what’s going on, and listen. Cops are murdering innocent Black people and People of Color, there is no justice being served, no accountability and the families of those people who were murdered are fighting every single day for justice, for an investment in their lives and in their communities. Wednesday is the day to show up and support them, make sure they know they are not alone, make sure they know that @ladaoffice Jackie Lacey WILL go!

node.text:
In a world where big corporations make a monthly commitment to all sorts of causes... I’m here to tell you PRIDE is day by day and it is personal... and it is radical. I’m excited to pair up with @trevorproject and @boy__smells for Boy Smells’ limited-edition Pride Collection, it’s all queer and all steeped in sharing your most authentic self with the world in ways that YOU discover, want, and need. Boy Smells is donating 10% of proceeds from their Pride collection to @TrevorProject through the month of July, with a minimum pledge of $100,000. Head to www.BoySmells.com to purchase your Ambrosia - made with mandarin peel, rosemary, galbanum, iris, hinoki, and vanilla. #PRIDEBoySmellsxTheTrevorProject #ismellbs #BoySmellsPartner 
Special shout out to @phlemuns for the fit ❤️

node.text: Finding this picture brought up a few different things, not seeing you for over a year means I’ve not been forced to take 100+ photos with you and although my wording suggests I hate that, I miss it more than anything and can’t wait for our newest selfie. You have one of the most radiant smiles and biggest hearts. I am a grateful younger brother, you’ve taught me what support looks like, you’ve shown me love in my darkest moments, and being proud of each other is one of the coolest parts of my life. You are a beautiful sister, a bad ass mother, and a patient, understanding, forgiving human being. Happy b(earth) day. I love you , Dani girl.

node.text:
Trans day of visibility. #transdayofvisibility How do we care about people who identify differently than we do?How do we show up for them? How do we manage our own beliefs and narratives to make sure not just ourselves and people who feel like ourselves are taken care of and loved? Today, it would be a beautiful thing to see more non- trans folks embracing the journey of visibility, what it looks like for someone who has always felt othered, what it looks like to put aside our own notions and privileges of being born in the bodies we feel most at home in,
It takes bravery and fortitude to take on a world that lacks understanding and empathy for someone to transition into ones own true existence.
Swipe for actions.

White supremacy is embedded in our culture and it is our duty to uproot it, call it out, and dismantle. Our media needs to call Tuesdays horrific massacre what it is, an act of terrorism. We have to stand with the Asian American community now and always. 
Understanding Robert Aaron Long is a terrorist and targeted Asian American women is essential, understanding that he was arrested peacefully whilst people like George Floyd and countless others were met with violence and murder is key in understanding that protection of only a specific type of person is the concern of law enforcement... sending love to the AAPI community and calling for accountability from myself, from law enforcement, from other white folks, from Hollywood, from big fashion corporation, from politicians and gun laws. Silence is just not a fucking option anymore.
